body_html:
tprof/internal/testdata is a tiny model in python/profiler/model_analyzer_test.py. However, there is no script to automatically regenerate the data. And regenerating the data would require change of test results (due to time/memory dynamics).

The tests don't affect save/restore model. So, it should be safe to disable in your environment.

tprof/internal/testdata is a tiny model in python/profiler/model_analyzer_test.py. However, there is no script to automatically regenerate the data. And regenerating the data would require change of test results (due to time/memory dynamics).

The tests don't affect save/restore model. So, it should be safe to disable in your environment.
